### `++fall`

Give unit a default value

Produces a default value `b` for a `++unit` `a` in cases where `a` is null.

Accepts
-------

`a` is a unit.

`b` is a noun that's used as the default value.

Produces
--------

Either a noun `b` or the unwrapped value of unit `a`.

Source
------

    ++  fall                                                ::  default
      |*  {a/(unit) b/*}
      ?~(a b u.a)


Examples
--------

    > (fall ~ `a`)
    `a`
    > (fall [~ u=0] `a`)
    0



